list_libraries(25.10)                                    list_libraries(25.10)

Name
       list_libraries - Lists all the libraries loaded in the session and used
       in the design

Syntax
       list_libraries

       [-help]

        [-power_domain <<string>>]

        [-used]

       [-used_analysis]

        [-view <<string>>]

       Lists all the libraries loaded in the session and used in the design.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -power_domain <<string>>
              Specifies  the  power  domain from which instances are to be se-
              lected.

       -used  Prints out a list of libraries used in the design  and  all  the
              other libraries, whose voltages match with those of the used li-
              braries (like vt variant libraries). This list is useful for ECO
              optimization.

       -used_analysis
              Prints out a list of used libraries in the design.

       -view <<string>>
              Specifies the view name whose libraries will be listed.

Examples
       Here are some examples.

              * The  following  command  reports all the libraries loaded in a
                session:

                > list_libraries

                Library Library Library  Group Name Path

                ------- ------- -------  max  fast  /home/fetiming/cte/regres-
                sions/data/libs/tsmc18/fast.lib

                min               slow              /home/fetiming/cte/regres-
                sions/data/libs/tsmc18/slow.lib

